Colombian Stocks: Petrominerales Declines; Ecopetrol Advances

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-12T20:25:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/colombian-stocks-petrominerales-declines-ecopetrol-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index was little changed at 13,417.83, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.1 percent to 1,629.90.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia â€™s largest  oil company ,
rose 0.8 percent to 3,865 pesos. The company said it found oil
in an exploratory well in the Cano Sur block with tests showing
an average production of 532 barrels per day, according to a
regulatory filing.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based oil company
with production and exploration in Colombia, fell 1.8 percent to
54,220 pesos.  The company said due to blockades around its Corcel
facilities, it has been unable to restart production operations
on the Corcel and Guatiquia Blocks, according to a regulatory
filing today. As a result, production totaling over 30,000
barrels of oil per day has been shut-in, the filing said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
